  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-06-30",
    "date": "2021-08-13T19:14:51Z",
    "text": "USA Workforce Tax Credit Act \n\nThis bill allows tax credits for charitable contributions to certain nonprofit organizations with the exclusive purpose of providing (1) workforce development and apprenticeship training, or (2) scholarships for elementary and secondary education expenses of students from households with income that does not exceed 200% of the median gross income.\n\nThe bill limits the credits to specified amounts for individuals and corporations. It also (1) imposes a tax on workforce development, apprenticeship training, and scholarship granting organizations that fail to distribute a specified portion of their receipts; and (2) establishes a $2 billion annual volume cap for the tax credits allowed under this bill."
  },
